collection.description: Conversations in Partnership with United Way of Dane County
collection.title: United Way of Dane County

highlights.description: Shelley reflects back on the impacts her work had on individuals and the community, while working at American Red Cross.
Adams reflects on his appreciation for Dane County and its forward thinking culture.
Shelley displays her concerns for the business of down town Madison.
Adam discusses his concerns for the homeless community in regards to COVID-19 and the cold weather.
David notes his concerns on transportation in Madison.
Bill discusses the importance of providing resources to those in need.
Bill recounts a story of his daughter buying a house outside of Madison and Dane County due to no affordable housing.
David notes the importance of individuals and group collaboration for the greater good of the people.
Bill highlights the importance of allowing different learning styles in schools.
Shelley shares the questions she has to help support her in making Dane County a better place to live.
